    <text type="note" xml:lang="ru" xml:id="letter-09064"> 
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date when-custom="1788-07-01">1788 г. июля 1.</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Пошли пожалуй к <rs ref="people.xml#ost05">вице-канцлеру</rs> сказать, что когда сумасшедшая <placeName ref="places.xml#swe01">шведская</placeName>, <persName ref="people.xml#sch05">Шляфом</persName> подписанная, нота <rs ref="people.xml#ost05">ему</rs> не нужна уже будет, чтоб <rs ref="people.xml#ost05">он</rs> ее на час ко мне прислал.
                <note type="editorial">
                    The note mentioned in this letter was sent in by the secretary of Swedish embassy <persName ref="people.xml#sch05">Schlaff</persName>. In this note the king of Sweden <persName ref="people.xml#gus01">Gustav III</persName> asked wheather there will be war or peace and proposed following conditions for the peace treaty: 1. To punish <persName ref="people.xml#raz02">count Razumovskii</persName> for his intrigues to revolt Swedish people; 2. To give to Sweden <placeName ref="places.xml#fin01">Finland</placeName> and the part of <placeName ref="places.xml#kar01">Karelia</placeName> to <placeName ref="places.xml#ses02">Systerbäck</placeName>, or all that what Sweden ceded to Russia by the <name type="event" ref="events.xml#abotre01">Treaty of Neustadt and Abo</name>; 3. To accept Gustav III's mediation in concluding peace treaty with <placeName ref="places.xml#ott0101">Porte</placeName> and to cede to Porte <placeName ref="places.xml#cri01">Crimea</placeName> and to restore the borderds as for 1768 before <name type="event" ref="events.xnl#turki01">the last war</name> (
                        <bibl>
                            <title ref="works.xml#dnevni02">Dnevnik A.V. Khrapovitskago s 18 ianvaria 1782 po 17 sentiabria 1793 goda</title>
                        , <biblScope unit="pp">pp. 58.</biblScope>
                    </bibl>
                    ).
                </note>
            </p>
        </body>
